title: Azealia Banks is working on new music with Fall Out Boy - Music
text: It looks like Azealia Banks may be collaborating with Fall Out Boy.The '212' rapper tweeted that the band had invited her to work with them, adding that she was "excited for you guys to hear it".Big Love to @falloutboy for inviting me to work with them!!!! I'm excited for you guys to hear it !!— azealiabanks (@AZEALIABANKS) October 16, 2015The group have just collaborated with Demi Lovato on a re-released version of their American Beauty/American Psycho track 'Irresistible'. © PA Images / Matt Sayles/APFall Out Boy at the 2015 MTV Movie Awards Banks recently criticised Nicki Minaj for her comments about Miley Cyrus at the MTV VMAs.Minaj originally said that Cyrus appropriated black culture while avoiding "what affects us, what is bothering us, what we feel is unfair to us". © Getty Images Banks then wrote on Twitter: "I wish Nic would stop trying to turn this Miley thing into a race issue cuz she was mute about cultural approp. until she became 'victim'."She also called out Minaj for complaining about "skinny women" and argued that "this isn't about race".
